note.body: To me border radius looked too big! Also I think there are no other things with that big rounded corners. I would prefer that rounded corners are consistent. Please use `10px` or maybe even `8px` (if you do, please change also `gf-popup-window`) to match window decoration radius.

> You need to add extra style to remove `border-radius` for cases when there is no compositor running.

The unlock dialog is just a [widget inside the screensaver window](https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gnome-flashback/-/blob/4eeb4cc4edc677d2fa4055f8629262b9c3481db0/gnome-flashback/libscreensaver/gf-window.c#L224), not an individual window, so the rounded corners are rendered correctly even if no compositor running.

> Also please use `10px` as border radius, same as `gf-popup-window`.

This dialog is much bigger than the `gf-popup-window` used for notifications, so I think it looks better with larger rounded corners.
